{"title_page": "List of Sydney FC managers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n[[Sydney FC|Sydney Football Club]] is an Australian professional [[association football]] club based in [[Moore Park, New South Wales|Moore Park]], Sydney. The club was formed in 2004. They became the first member from the NSW admitted inro the [[A-League]] along with the [[Central Coast Mariners FC|Central Coast Mariners]] and the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].\n\nThere have been nine permanent and one [[Caretaker manager|caretaker managers]] of Sydney FC since 2005; [[Steve Corica]] has managed the club in two separate spells; once as a caretaker, once as a permanent manager.\n\n\n[[Sydney FC]] are a football club based in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]] who were founded in 2004. They have had nine different managers in their history including one caretaker who came back as a manager. Their first manager being [[Pierre Littbarski]] and the current being [[Steve Corica]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aleaguestats.com/A-League_6SydneyFC.html|title=ALeagueStats|website=www.aleaguestats.com|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n\n==Managers==\n* Manager dates and statistics are sourced from ''WorldFootball.net'' for Littbarski to Farina,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aus.worldfootball.net/teams/sydney-fc/9/|title=Sydney FC's managers|website=WorldFootball.net}}</ref> and ''Soccerbase'' thereafter for Arnold and Corica.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=4534&comp_id=311&teamTabs=managers|title=Sydney FC Manager History|website=Soccerbase}}</ref> Names of caretaker managers are supplied where known, and periods of caretaker management are highlighted in ''italics'' and marked {{dagger|alt=caretaker}}, depending on the scenaro. Win percentage is rounded to two decimal places.\n* Only first-team competitive matches are counted. Wins, losses and draws are results at the final whistle; the results of [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-outs]] are not counted.\n* Statistics are complete up to and including the match played on 21 March 2020.\n\n'''Key'''\n*M = matches played; W = matches won; D = matches drawn; L = matches lost; GF = Goals for; GA = Goals against; Win % = percentage of total matches won\n*{{legend2|#B0C4DE||border=1px solid #AAAAAA}} {{dagger|alt=caretaker}} Managers with this background and symbol in the \"Name\" column are italicised to denote caretaker appointments.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+List of Sydney FC managers\n!width=11%|Name\n!width=11%|Nationality!!From!!To!!M!!W!!D!!L!!GF!!GA!!Win %!!class=\"unsortable\"|Honours !!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:left|{{sortname|Pierre|Littbarski}}\n|align=left|{{flagu|Germany}}\n|align=left|{{dts|26 February 2005}}\n|align=left|{{dts|3 May 2006}}\n{{WDL|38|23|8|7|for=79|against=33}}\n|align=left|OFC Club Championship winners: [[2005 OFC Club Championship|2005]]<br/>A-League champions: [[2006 A-League Grand Final|2006]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:left|{{sortname|Terry|Butcher}}\n|align=left|{{flagu|England}}\n|align=left|{{dts|1 July 2006}}\n|align=left|{{dts|7 February 2007}}\n{{WDL|29|13|9|7|for=41|against=19}}\n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:left|{{sortname|Branko|\u010culina}}\n|align=left|{{flagu|Croatia}}\n|align=left|{{dts|8 February 2007}}\n|align=left|{{dts|22 October 2007}}\n{{WDL|24|7|9|8|for=69|against=82}}\n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:left|{{sortname|John|Kosmina}}\n|align=left|{{flagu|Australia}}\n|align=left|{{dts|25 November 2007}}\n|align=left|{{dts|25 January 2009}}\n{{WDL|34|12|9|13|for=52|against=45}}\n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:left|{{sortname|Vitezslav|Lavicka}}\n|align=left|{{flagu|Czech Republic}}\n|align=left|{{dts|1 February 2009}}\n|align=left|{{dts|30 June 2012}}\n{{WDL|113|36|24|53|for=123|a